  "text": "Environmental consumption has often proved to be at variance with sustainability particularly among the high income societies (Hobson,2003; [CITATION_1] .This particular concern has provided contrasts between the high and low income societies. The 1998 human development report, Consumption for Human Development, provided linkages with sustainability and environmental consumption. It recounts that \"environmental damage threatens both the earth's carrying capacity and people's coping capacity. And it may have serious consequences for future generations\" (UNDP, 1998).",
